# Bundled Tauri sidecars live here.
#
# Build the AXL Go binary per-target and drop it under the canonical
# Tauri sidecar naming (target triple suffix, plus `.exe` on Windows):
#
#   axl-aarch64-apple-darwin
#   axl-x86_64-apple-darwin
#   axl-x86_64-pc-windows-msvc.exe
#   axl-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu
#
# Same naming convention for `0g-storage-client-<target>` (added by the
# `zerog-memory` plan step). Tauri's `externalBin` (see
# `tauri.conf.json`) and the sidecar lifecycle code in
# `src-tauri/src/sidecar.rs` reference these files; they are
# intentionally not committed.
#
# A helper script that downloads release artifacts from the AXL repo and
# drops them here lands as part of the `bootstrap-nodes` plan step.
